  "text": "Three extracts of CP were subjected to DPPH radical scavenging assay. All extracts showed antioxidant activity which, in the present case, is directly proportional to the concentration ( fig. 2A ). At 800 µg/ml, CP leaf extract (P>0.05) exhibited the highest activity among the extracts, comparable to the reference compound, ascorbic acid. It also showed the lowest IC 50 value (10.46+2.13 µg/ml) ( Table 1) , which denotes the highest antioxidant activity among the three extracts. A low IC 50 value indicates high antioxidant activity [CITATION_1] .",
